    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-17T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-17T07:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.6215/26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-17T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >February 17, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 17—2:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>295. My 51, January 11. <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi> and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Izvestiya</hi> of February 16 report the arrival in Moscow on February 15
                    of a German delegation to the Central Joint Soviet-German Frontier Commission
                    for the demarcation of the Soviet-German frontier from the River Igorka to the
                    Baltic Sea. The delegation which is reported as consisting of six members was
                    met at the station by members of the Soviet delegation to the Commission
                    mentioned and by officials of the German Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
